py-error=\"Copy failed! Use Ctrl + C instead.\" data-prismjs-copy-success=\"Copied!\"><div class=\"zDocsTopicPageBodyContent wide\" dir=\"ltr\"><div id=\"zDocsAiSummaryContaineruniface_104zuy1665702794567.html\"></div><div><article class=\"hascomments\" data-page=\"bundle:uniface_104/enus/zuy1665702794567.html\" id=\"bundle:uniface_104/enus/zuy1665702794567.html\"><main role=\"main\"><article aria-labelledby=\"ariaid-title1\" class=\"dita\" id=\"zuy1665702794567\" role=\"article\">\n<h1 class=\"title topictitle1\" id=\"ariaid-title1\">\n      Resource Browser (Define Structure)\n </h1>\n<div class=\"body refbody\"><p class=\"shortdesc\">Use the Resource Browser to create or select entities and fields in the component structure.\n </p>\n<section class=\"section\" id=\"zuy1665702794567__section_w3434ab1b7b1_w3435ab1b7_w3436ab1\">\n<p class=\"p\"></p>\n</section>\n<section class=\"section\" id=\"zuy1665702794567__section_kq2_n32_5cc\"><h2 class=\"title sectiontitle\" id=\"d570138e60\">Tabs</h2>\n<ul class=\"ul\" id=\"zuy1665702794567__ul_hkf_432_5cc\">\n<li class=\"li\" id=\"zuy1665702794567__li_d2585e1_d2586e1_d2587e1\"><span class=\"ph uicontrol\">Templates</span>—use templates to\n               create component entities and fields that do not have database access. Inserting an\n               object from the Templates tab creates a copy that you can then rename. </li>\n<li class=\"li\" id=\"zuy1665702794567__li_d2588e1_d2589e1_d2590e1\"><span class=\"ph uicontrol\">Model</span>—use modeled entities\n               and their fields to create derived component entities that access a data store.\n               Inserting a modeled entity or field creates a component entity or field that inherits\n               from the modeled object. </li>\n</ul>\n</section>\n<section class=\"section\" id=\"zuy1665702794567__section_bmt_432_5cc\"><h2 class=\"title sectiontitle\" id=\"d570138e79\">How to</h2>\n<ul class=\"ul\" id=\"zuy1665702794567__ul_z3p_p32_5cc\">\n<li class=\"li\" id=\"zuy1665702794567__li_d2591e1_d2592e1_d2593e1\"><a class=\"xref\" data-bundleid=\"uniface_104\" data-navpath=\"flj1690357335479.html\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/flj1690357335479.html\" title=\"You can select templates, modeled objects, and code snippets in the Resource Browser and add them to current object. You can drag and drop objects, or use the context menu.\">Add Objects from the Resource Browser</a>\n</li>\n<li class=\"li\" id=\"zuy1665702794567__li_d2594e1_d2595e1_d2596e1\"><a class=\"xref\" data-bundleid=\"uniface_104\" data-navpath=\"yed1704964703330.html\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/yed1704964703330.html\" title=\"The number of objects available for selection in the Resource Browser may be very large, so you can filter the content in a variety of ways, depending on context.\">Filter and Search for Objects in Resource Browser</a>\n</li>\n<li class=\"li\" id=\"zuy1665702794567__li_d2597e1_d2598e1_d2599e1\"><a class=\"xref\" data-bundleid=\"uniface_104\" data-navpath=\"zii1704964501123.html\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/zii1704964501123.html\" title=\"For services and server pages, use the Define Structure worksheet to add and organize entities and fields in the component structure.\">Define the Component Structure</a>\n</li>\n</ul>\n</section>\n</div>\n</article></main></article>\n</div></div></div><div class=\"bottomFeedback\"><div aria-labelledby=\"bottomFeedbackText\" class=\"bottomFeedbackContent\" role=\"group\"><span class=\"bottomFeedbackText\" id=\"bottomFeedbackText\">Was this topic helpful?</span><div class=\"bottomFeedbackButtonGroup\"><a data-backdrop=\"static\" data-target=\"#feedbackModal_bottom_8424526\" data-toggle=\"modal\" href=\"#\" role=\"button\" type=\"button\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-thumbs-up\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-thumbs-up\"></use></svg><span>Like</span></a><a data-backdrop=\"static\" data-target=\"#feedbackModal_bottom_8424526\" data-toggle=\"modal\" href=\"#\" role=\"button\" type=\"button\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-thumbs-down\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-thumbs-down\"></use></svg><span>Dislike</span></a></div></div></div><div style=\"position: fixed; bottom: 170px; right: 70px; cursor: pointer; transition-duration: 0.2s; transition-timing-function: linear; transition-delay: 0s; z-index: 3; opacity: 0; visibility: hidden; transition-property: opacity, visibility;\"><button aria-label=\"Scroll to top\" class=\"zDocsScrollTopBtn\" data-tooltip-content=\"Scroll to top\" data-tooltip-id=\"zDocsBackToTopToolTip\" id=\"zDocsScrollToTop\" type=\"button\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-next\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-next\"></use></svg></button></div></body></html>", "text": "Resource Browser (Define Structure) Add to My Topics Add selected topic and subtopics Add Topic & Subtopics with topic head Add entire publication Watch Download PDF Save selected topic Save selected topic and subtopics Save entire publication Share Email Link Copy Link Feedback Last Updated Sept 20, 2024 Summarize Uniface 10.4 Resource Browser (Define Structure) Use the Resource Browser to create or select entities and fields in the component structure. Tabs Templates —use templates to create component entities and fields that do not have database access. Inserting an object from the Templates tab creates a copy that you can then rename. Model —use modeled entities and their fields to create derived component entities that access a data store. Inserting a modeled entity or field creates a component entity or field that inherits from the modeled object. How to Add Objects from the Resource Browser Filter and Search for Objects in Resource Browser Define the Component Structure Was this topic helpful? Like Dislike"}